<https://example.com/mlops/mlops> dcterms:description "An ontology modeling the abstract concepts, processes, and roles involved in Machine Learning Operations (MLOps). It captures the lifecycle of ML systems, including development, deployment, monitoring, and maintenance, while distinguishing MLOps from traditional DevOps due to the probabilistic nature of ML outputs. The ontology is designed to support SMEs and other organizations in structuring MLOps processes, roles, tools, and artifacts." .
